-- PGE Is Preparing Zloty, Euro Bond Sales `Far Above' $627.8 Million Each
-- David McQuaid
-- 2010-07-21T07:34:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/pge-is-preparing-zloty-euro-bond-sales-far-above-627-8-million-each.html

          
          
             PGE SA, Poland’s largest electricity
producer, is preparing sales of zloty-denominated corporate
bonds and euro-denominated bonds, each of which may raise “far
above” 2 billion zloty ($627.8 million), PGE Chief Executive
Officer Tomasz Zadroga said today in an interview on TVN CNBC
Biznes television.  
          
          


  


        